Meeting healthcare demands in Africa is no easy feat, being the second-most-populous continent with the greatest deficit in healthcare infrastructure. But as countries in the region race to meet the targets set for the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) by 2030 – to explore ways to get better health outcomes on the continent, Eyong Ebai GE, Healthcare’s General Manager for West-Central Africa and French Sub-Saharan Africa joins CNBC Africa’s Esther Awoniyi....